  "local_port": 44648,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some good colleges for pursuing MBA in hotel management or hospitality management in Hyderabad?",
  "response": "If you're considering pursuing an MBA in Hotel Management or Hospitality Management in Hyderabad, here are some notable institutions that offer quality programs in these fields:\n\n1. **Indian School of Business (ISB) Hyderabad**  \n   - While ISB primarily focuses on general management, it offers elective courses and specialization opportunities in various sectors, including hospitality management.\n   - Known for its world-class faculty, infrastructure, and alumni network.\n\n2. **ICFAI Business School (IBS) Hyderabad**  \n   - Offers an MBA program with specializations in various fields, including hospitality management.\n   - Emphasizes practical learning and industry exposure.\n\n3. **Jawaharlal Nehru Technological University (JNTU) Hyderabad**  \n   - Offers an MBA program with opportunities to specialize in hospitality and tourism management.\n   - Known for its strong academic curriculum and industry collaborations.\n\n4. **Institute of Hotel Management, Catering Technology & Applied Nutrition (IHM), Hyderabad**  \n   - Specializes in hospitality and hotel management education.\n   - Offers diploma and degree programs, including MBA-equivalent courses in hospitality management.\n\n5. **Acharya Nagarjuna University (ANU) Centre for Distance Education**  \n   - Offers distance learning MBA programs with specializations in hospitality and tourism management.\n   - Suitable for working professionals seeking flexibility.\n\n6. **St. Mary\u2019s College of Hotel Management, Hyderabad**  \n   - Focuses exclusively on hospitality and hotel management education.\n   - Offers postgraduate programs with a strong emphasis on practical training and industry exposure.\n\n7. **National Academy of Hotel Management & Tourism (NAHMCT) Hyderabad**  \n   - Specializes in hospitality and tourism management programs.\n   - Provides industry-aligned curriculum and internship opportunities.\n\n8. **Vignana Jyothi Institute of Management (VJIM) Hyderabad**  \n   - Offers an MBA program with elective courses in hospitality management.\n   - Known for its focus on entrepreneurial and management skills.\n\n9. **Osmania University, Department of Business Management**  \n   - Offers an MBA program with specializations in tourism and hospitality management.\n   - One of the oldest and most reputed universities in Hyderabad.\n\nBefore selecting a college, consider factors like program structure, faculty expertise, industry connections, placement records, and campus facilities. Additionally, check if the program aligns with your career goals and interests.",
